\begin_layout Standard
The calculations of expected returns are highly sensitive to the choice
 of prior, and impact the ultimate decision on whether to play the games.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}e(8,8)$
\end_inset

 prior would have had me optimistic about playing either game, while the
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{B}e(7,13)$
\end_inset

 prior would have resulted in both games seeming fairly risky.
